worksheet.exercise:
					Compute the domain of the following functions


f(x) = \sqrt{2x-5} 

g(x) = \frac{1}{x^2-1} 




We need 2x-5\geq 0 so that the value under the square root is nonnegative. This means that 2x\geq5 and hence x\geq2.5 is the domain of the function f

We need x^2-1\neq 0, so we should ask when it is zero. It is zero when x^2=1 or x=\pm 1. Thus the domain is all real numbers except for 1 or -1

					The population of Forks, Washington was 3060 in the year 1980 and grew by 3.4\% each year.    


How many people lived in Forks in 1981? 1982?

Write a formula for population P as a function of time t since 1980.

What is predicted for the population in the year 2013?





To get the number of people in Forks in 1981 and 1982 we increase by 3.4% once and twice respectively.
							\text{Pop in 1981} = 3060\cdot 1.034 \approx 3164 \text{ people} 
							\text{Pop in 1982} = 3060\cdot 1.034^2 \approx 3272 \text{ people} 

 P = f(t) = 3060 (1.034)^t 

 f(33) = 3060(1.034)^{33}\approx 9224\text{ people}

The population of manatees in the Gulf of Mexico was 1200 in the year 2010 and 1600 in the year 2018.
Write a formula for population P of manatees as a linear function of time t since 2010.
Write a formula for population P of manatees as an exponential function of time t since 2010.
What is predicted for the population in the year 2020?
Computing the slope we get m = \frac{1600-1200}{8-0} = 50 \text{ manatees/year}
Putting it all together, we get that P = 1200+50t
To start with, we know that it is of the form P=ab^t where in this case a=1200. Using the fact that when t=8, P=1600 we see that 1600=1200b^8 \quad \Rightarrow \quad \frac{1600}{1200}=b^8 \quad \Rightarrow \quad b = \sqrt[8]{\frac 43} P = 1200\left( \sqrt[8]{\frac 43} \right)^t
Using the linear model, we get P = 1200+50(10) = 1700\text{ manatees}
Using the exponential model, we get P = 1200\left( \sqrt[8]{\frac 43} \right)^{10} \approx 1719 \text{ manatees}

					If you invest $1200 in an account accrues interest at a rate of 5% compounded continuously, how long will it take for the balance to reach $1600?


The formula for the account balance is
						B = 1200e^{0.05t}

We want to know when it reaches $1600, so we set B to 1600 and solve for t.
						 1600 = 1200 e^{0.05t} \quad \Rightarrow \quad \frac{1600}{1200} = e^{0.05t} \quad \Rightarrow \quad \ln\left(\frac{1600}{1200}\right) = \ln(e^{0.05t})=0.05t 
						 t = \frac{\ln\left(\frac{1600}{1200}\right) }{0.05}


The technology company Orange started selling its oPhone in 2015 with sales of 10000 oPhones. By 2018 it sold 500000 oPhones. Model the growth of oPhone sales using an exponential function of the form
   					f(t)= ae^{kt} 
  					where t is time in years since 2015.


We start with the fact that we know  f(t)=10000e^{kt} as the initial quantity was 10000. Then we use that when t=3, the number of phones is 500000.
						500000=10000e^{k\cdot 3} \quad \Rightarrow \quad 50 = e^{3k} 
						 \ln(50)=\ln(e^{3k})=3k \quad \Rightarrow \quad k = \frac{\ln(50)}{3} \approx 1.30401

 Putting it all together, we get
						 f(t) = 10000e^{1.30401t}
